1551122501-How.to.Disappear.Completely--.title: How.to.Disappear.Completely--Lilly.Ryan--Linux.Conf.Au.2019.mp4
1551122501-How.to.Disappear.Completely--.description:
This talk {34 mins} provides an overview of facial recognition & ways to foil it.You’ll learn the ways machines “see” us, and how to play with them in order to become invisible. We’ll dive into the ethics of biometric identification, the way current legislation affects this technology, and what is needed for facial recognition technology to be both useful and just.

Lilly Ryan is a pen tester, Python wrangler, and recovering historian from Melbourne.

Linux.Conf.Au
2019-January-22
New Zealand--Christchurch--University of Canterbury
https://2019.linux.conf.au/schedule/presentation/250/
